{
  "stem": "14251.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I remember on one of the mornings, just two, three days before the Russians came, we had a wooden sled that we would play with.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I remember using the sled, lying on my stomach, and sledding up to this thing, which turned out to be later a grenade, an-- an-- an unexploded grenade.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Maybe it would never have exploded, and then, again, maybe it would.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And of course, I-- I picked it up, looked at it lying on my stomach on the sled, and someone yelled, throw that away.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I don't know who it was.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was an adult-sounding voice.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So some of the grenades had already landed there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And at night, you could see red in the distance.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "You know, it was coming close.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "You could hear it, and the ground was vibrating.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We all had to put our ears to the ground to see how close this was.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And so on one of our nights, while we were among the potato sacks trying to sleep, each with our clothes on, as many as we could put on, somehow in the early morning I remember I looked up, and the-- the lid-- where you went into the cellar was there's a lid, which is the floor of the upstairs.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And then you come down some huge steps, and you're in this little cellar.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And the first thing I see is this lid is coming open.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And it's obviously very, very early because the color of this-- the light is-- is like a snowy day before the snow and early, early.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And I see these bayonets.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And they're talking something we can't understand.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "We all looked at each other.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And they knew one word, which was raus, out, meaning come out.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
